Gene Wolfe has a beautiful short story series about a Nebraskan folklorist I recommend, but that aside, it's impotent to remember that, yes, European folklore also knows both skinwalkers and bigfoots. It's a perennial thing, even if the taxonomy is classified a bit differently.
Khazar (Jewish state) and Quasar (astronomy) etymologically related

A few interesting fragments from Halton Arp's atlas. He supported a revisionist astronomic theory, where Quasars were not unbelievably distant reactions, but far closer, star-like objects, "emissions" from galaxies, that eventually turned into systems of their own. PDF available.
Not my sphere (literally), but Halton Arp seems interesting as a figure

Reading through a 1993 Internet forum/email discussion group that Dr. Peat participated in 1999 and laughing at people spamming: "IF YOU RECEIVE AN EMAIL THAT SAYS: IT TAKES GUTS TO SAY "JESUS", DO NOT OPEN IT, IT'S A VIRUS AND WILL DELETE YOUR HARD DRIVE !", early Internet days.

Like the messages claim that the IBM sent a warning that morning, others who were more tech-savy tell them it's probably a hoax and there's no way an email could do that, it's the online dawn of misinformation and trolling people. No one even thinks of computer virsuses nowadays.
